news.title: BMC can spare five acres of Mulund octroi land for Dharavi redevelopment
news.para: At the time, BJP politicians, including deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis, party candidate from Mumbai North East Mihir Kotecha and former MP Kirit Somaiya, had stressed that they would not allow the relocation of Dharavi residents to Mulund.

news.title: Experion Developers acquires 7.81-acre land in Gurugram for Rs 400 crore
news.para: The wholly owned Indian subsidiary of Singapore's Experion Holdings Pte Ltd had in the last one-and-a-half years acquired five plots worth Rs 2,100 crore, mainly in Gurugram, where it is in the process of launching new projects.

news.title: Raymond to demerge real estate business, list it on exchanges
news.para: The standalone operational revenue of the real estate division stood at Rs 1,592.65 crore in the last fiscal, accounting for 24 per cent of the total revenue of Raymond Ltd.
